Package com.example.geoquizfrontend

Class SlimCallback<T>

java.lang.Object
com.example.geoquizfrontend.SlimCallback<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the type of the response body
All Implemented Interfaces:
retrofit2.Callback<T>
public class SlimCallback<T> extends Object implements retrofit2.Callback<T>
SlimCallback is a class that implements the Callback interface from Retrofit. It is a generic class that can handle responses from Retrofit calls. It takes a LambdaInterface as a parameter in its constructor, which is used to perform an action on the response body. It also takes an optional custom log tag for logging purposes.

      public void onResponse(retrofit2.Call<T> call, retrofit2.Response<T> response)
      This method is called when a response is received from a Retrofit call. If the response is successful, it performs an action on the response body using the LambdaInterface. If the response is not successful, it logs the response code and message.
